The Minister of the Federal Ministry of Labour and Employment Dr. Chris Ngige, has inaugurated  the Board of  the Nigerian Social Insurance Trust Fund (NSITF) under the Chairmanship of Mr. Austine Enejamo-Isire. Mr. Isire, is a chartered accountant, Fellow, Institute of Chartered Accountants of Nigeria (ICAN) and renowned insurance expert, Senior Member, Chartered Institute of Insurance of Nigeria (CIIN). He is also a member of the chartered Institute of Bankers of Nigeria (CIBN) and Chartered Institute of Taxation of Nigeria (CITN) was approved by Mr. President for this position. Details later… Ngige inaugurates NSITF board, Kokori redeployed to institute BREAKING: Presidency resolves NSITF tussle, appoints Kokori as Michael Imoudu board's chair PHOTO SPEAK: Ngige inaugurates Austine Enejamo-Isire led NSITF board Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin